<div class="muted header-note">
        I can answer 3 questions:
    <ul>
        <li><i>How much experience do you have?</i></li>
        <li><i>What does your team do?</i></li>
        <li><i>How is your media outreach?</i></li>
    </ul>
    <small>
        Remember, this is a single video, so I DO NOT have "idle state" video, and I have to start and pause at certain times, so it's the not the best experience, but that's all I can do without actual videos.
    </small>
</div>

<div class="text-input">
    <input
           on-keydown="inputKeydown"
           type="text"
           placeholder="Type your question here or click on the mic and say it.">
</div>

<div class="player">
    <video autoplay src="{{ (root || '') + (answer.media || '') }}" poster="{{ (root || '') + (answer.poster || '/media/fake.png')}}"></video>
    <img
            on-click="micToggle"
            src="{{root || ''}}/img/mic.png"
            class="mic {{#if !recognizing && mic.on}}hand mic-on{{else}}mic-off{{/if}}"/>
</div>

{{#if transcript}}
    <div class="transcript">I think you said: <span class="muted">"{{transcript}}"</span></div>
{{/if}}

{{#if answer.answer}}
    <blockquote class="answer muted">Short answer: "{{answer.answer}}"</blockquote>
{{/if}}